<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="724" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="16.[1469,2676,1198,1822]" pageId="16" pageNumber="724">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1472,1818,1631,1664]" pageId="16" pageNumber="724">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Samar Squirrel is considered an agricultural pest in some places, damaging corn and sweet potato crops. Major threats are not known, but it is illegally traded as a pet and hunted for local consumption.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
